'''2017年女性大游行'''（{{lang-en|2017 Women's March}}）是自2017年1月21－22日在世界各地进行的一系列[[女权|女权]][[游行示威|游行示威]]活动，旨在捍卫[[女权|女权]]，同时为移民改革、科学精神、健保改革、环境保护、[[LGBT权益|LGBT权益]]、种族公义、世俗化运动、堕胎权益发声。这些游行示威活动直指新任[[美国总统|美国总统]][[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]的一系列言论和立场：一些人认为其涉及性別歧視、種族歧視、排外及反伊斯蘭等言論，加上不認同其是合法總統，以其他方式值得谴责。{{efn|此前川普在2005年曾夸口言其能在未经允许的情况下抓女性[[生殖器|阴部]]，称“只要你是名人，她們就讓你做，想做什么都行，比如抓她们的下体”。英文原文为“{{lang|en|When you're a star they let you do it, you can do anything, grab 'em by the pussy}}”}}<ref name="FT 100,000" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN1550DW|title=In challenge to Trump, women protesters swarm streets across U.S.|date=2017-01-22|newspaper=Reuters|access-date=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122000623/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN1550DW|dead-url=no}}</ref>

其间首次抗议发生于[[美国|美国]][[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿哥伦比亚特区]]，并被称作'''华盛顿女性大游行'''（{{lang|en|Women's March on Washington}}）。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/culture/jia-tolentino/the-somehow-controversial-womens-march-on-washington|title=The Somehow Controversial Women's March on Washington|last=Tolentino|first=Jia|date=2017-01-18|website=The New Yorker|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170120032957/http://www.newyorker.com/culture/jia-tolentino/the-somehow-controversial-womens-march-on-washington|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Bosman|first=Julie|title=In a Rust Belt Town, the Women's March Draws Shrugs and Cheers From Afar|website=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|date=2017-01-21|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/niles-michigan-trump-no-women-march.html|ref=harv|accessdate=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122030157/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/niles-michigan-trump-no-women-march.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>此次游行示威作为[[草根|草根]]运动在唐纳德·川普于同年1月20日[[2017年美國總統就職典禮|就任]]的第二天开始，旨在“向执政当局上台的第一天发出直接信息、告诉世界女权即人权”、对川普的被指侵犯女性的言论与行为进行抗議。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/16/politics/womens-march-on-washington-need-to-know/index.html|title=Women's March on Washington: What you need to know|last=Tatum|first=Sophie|publisher=CNN|date=2017-01-16|access-date=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170119234926/http://www.cnn.com/2017/01/16/politics/womens-march-on-washington-need-to-know/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>参与华盛顿游行的人数至少为现场参与前一天就职典礼的人数三倍。<ref name="Wallace">{{cite news|title=Crowd Scientists Say Women's March in Washington Had 3 Times as Many People as Trump's Inauguration|last1=Wallace|first1=Tim|last2=Parlapiano|first2=Alicia|date=2017-01-22|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2017-01-22|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/22/us/politics/womens-march-trump-crowd-estimates.html|archive-date=2017-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170313210125/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/22/us/politics/womens-march-trump-crowd-estimates.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[YouTube|YouTube]]<ref name="YouTube">{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XC9hTrX9oNk&feature=player_embedded |title=Women's March on Washington |accessdate=2017-01-23 |archive-date=2017-01-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122122227/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XC9hTrX9oNk&feature=player_embedded |dead-url=no }}Live stream of Women's March on Washington</ref>、[[Facebook|Facebook]]及[[Twitter|Twitter]]等社交网站上均有直播位於華盛頓的遊行。<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.womensmarch.com/ |title=Women's March on Washington |quote=You can view the program live on a number of Jumbotrons on Independence Ave. and through all of our social media platforms, Facebook, Twitter, and YouTube. |website=Women's March |accessdate=2017-01-21 |archive-date=2017-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129062214/https://www.womensmarch.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

游行示威在全世界各地均有发生，仅美国境内便有民众计划了408次示威活动，美国以外也有168次。<ref name="auto7">{{citation|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/17/us/womens-march.html|title=Where Women's Marches Are|last=Schmidt|first=Kierstein|last2=Almukhtar|first2=Sarah|newspaper=New York Times|date=2017-01-20|access-date=2017-01-21|archive-date=2017-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121084623/https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/17/us/womens-march.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>活动的组织者之后表示，全球范围内共有673场游行，其中墨西哥有20场，加拿大有29场。<ref name="FT 100,000"/>在首都华盛顿哥伦比亚特区就至少有50万民众参与，初步估计全球参与人数超过2百万。<ref name="FT 100,000">{{Cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/7b34cd82-dfe2-11e6-8405-9e5580d6e5fb|title=Hundreds of thousands gather in US cities for Women's March|last1=Weaver|first1=Courtney|last2=Rennison|first2=Joe|last3=Whipp|first3=Lindsay|last4=Bullock|first4=Nicole|date=2017-01-22|work=Financial Times|accessdate=2017-01-22|via=|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122050503/https://www.ft.com/content/7b34cd82-dfe2-11e6-8405-9e5580d6e5fb|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto8">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/womens-march.html|title='We're Not Going Away': Huge Crowds for Women's Marches Against Trump|last=Alcindor|first=Anemona Hartocollis, Yamiche|date=2017-01-21|last2=Chokshi|first2=Niraj|newspaper=New York Times|issn=0362-4331|accessdate=2017-01-21|archive-date=2019-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191125175923/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/womens-march.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="auto9">{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2017/01/21/womens-march-aims-start-movement-trump-inauguration/96864158|title=At 2.5 million strong, Women's Marches crush expectations|work=USA Today|date=2017-01-21|accessdate=2017-01-22|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122002531/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2017/01/21/womens-march-aims-start-movement-trump-inauguration/96864158/|dead-url=no}}</ref>此次游行为美国自1964年的{{link-en|反越南战争游行|Opposition to United States involvement in the Vietnam War}}以来境内发生过最大规模的示威活动。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/22/donald-trump-kellyanne-conway-inauguration-alternative-facts|title=Trump presidency begins with defense of false 'alternative facts'|first=Jon|last=Swaine|date=2017-01-22|publisher=|via=The Guardian|accessdate=2017-01-23|archive-date=2017-01-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170123215326/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/jan/22/donald-trump-kellyanne-conway-inauguration-alternative-facts|dead-url=no}}</ref>

游行在华盛顿特区、芝加哥、[[洛杉矶|洛杉矶]]（组织者聲称有750,000人参与）<ref>{{cite web|title=Shaded pink, women's protest fills the streets of downtown L.A.|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/california/la-me-la-ln-womens-march-20170121-story.html|website=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=2017-01-24|archive-date=2017-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171229063841/http://www.latimes.com/local/california/la-me-la-ln-womens-march-20170121-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>、纽约、西雅图大约共有两百万人参与，但无人被捕。<ref name="Zero Arrests">{{cite news|url= http://www.citylab.com/politics/2017/01/no-arrests-at-womens-march-in-dc-los-angeles-new-york-chicago-austin-seattle/514067/|title= Millions of Marchers, Zero Arrests|work= Citylab|last= Capps|first= Kriston|date= January 22, 2017|accessdate= January 23, 2017|archive-date= 2017-01-23|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20170123055400/http://www.citylab.com/politics/2017/01/no-arrests-at-womens-march-in-dc-los-angeles-new-york-chicago-austin-seattle/514067/|dead-url= no}}</ref>
