== 背景 ==

=== 组织者 ===
2016年11月9日，在川普被確定獲選為美國總統後<ref>{{cite news|last1=Novick|first1=Ilana|title=March on Washington and beyond: How women are resisting Donald Trump|url=http://www.salon.com/2017/01/02/march-on-washington-and-beyond-how-women-are-resisting-donald-trump_partner|accessdate=January 4, 2017|work=Salon|date=January 2, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103172050/http://www.salon.com/2017/01/02/march-on-washington-and-beyond-how-women-are-resisting-donald-trump_partner/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，來自[[夏威夷|夏威夷]]的Teresa Shook在臉書上創建了一個活動，並邀請其朋友去華盛頓遊行抗議，作為對川普當選為美國總統和對其政治觀點的反應{{efn|"Born of one woman's invitation to forty friends, the event is meant as a rejoinder to the fact that a candidate with a troubling history regarding women's rights—one who actually bragged about committing sexual assault—has made it to the White House."<ref>{{cite news|author=Cobb, Jelani|title=The Return of Civil Disobedience|url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/01/09/the-return-of-civil-disobedience|work=The New Yorker|date=January 9, 2017|access-date=January 3, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170103051017/http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2017/01/09/the-return-of-civil-disobedience|dead-url=no}}; and "bragged about sexual assault," see, e.g., [[Donald_Trump_and_Billy_Bush_recording|Donald Trump and Billy Bush recording]].</ref>}}<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.wmagazine.com/story/womens-march-on-washington-activists-organizers|title=The Women of the Women's March: Meet the Activists Who Are Planning One of the Largest Demonstrations in American History|magazine=W Magazine|date=January 19, 2017|first1=Katherine|last1=Cusumano|accessdate=January 21, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170121062541/http://www.wmagazine.com/story/womens-march-on-washington-activists-organizers|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。之後Evvie Harmon、Fontaine Pearson、Bob Bland、Breanne Butler也創建了類似的臉書活動，並迅速獲得上千名女性的簽名參與<ref name="WMOW Explained" /><ref>{{cite news|author=Kearney, Laila|title=Hawaii grandma's plea launches women's march in Washington|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN13U0GW|agency=Reuters|date=December 5, 2016|accessdate=December 29, 2016|archive-date=2017-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170130235209/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-trump-women-idUSKBN13U0GW|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Wulfhorst, Ellen|title=Trump Inauguration To Be Met By Mass 'Women's March on Washington'|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-million-women-march_us_582642efe4b0c4b63b0cbfa5/|work=The Huffington Post|date=November 11, 2016|access-date=December 30, 2016|archive-date=2017-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170106212940/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/trump-million-women-march_us_582642efe4b0c4b63b0cbfa5|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Cauterucci, Christina|title=Getting the Women's March on Washington on the Road|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/life/doublex/2016/11/the_women_s_march_on_washington_faces_uncertain_logistics_on_inauguration.html|work=[[Slate_(magazine)|Slate]]|date=November 23, 2016|access-date=December 30, 2016|archive-date=2016-12-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161229122606/http://www.slate.com/articles/life/doublex/2016/11/the_women_s_march_on_washington_faces_uncertain_logistics_on_inauguration.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Harmon、Pearson和Butler決定整合他們的活動，並開始創建了華盛頓女性大遊行的官網<ref name="WMOW Explained">{{Cite news|url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/politics-government/election/article116642998.html|title=Explaining the Women's March on Washington|publisher=McClatchyDC|date=November 23, 2017|accessdate=January 23, 2017|archive-date=2017-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202012006/http://www.mcclatchydc.com/news/politics-government/election/article116642998.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。為了確保運動具有不同種族和背景人士的廣泛代表性，運動的聯合發起人和行動負責人Vanessa Wruble邀請Tamika D. Mallory、Carmen Perez、Linda Sarsour和Bob Bland一同加入<ref name="WMOW Explained" /><ref name=":1">{{cite web|url=https://www.womensmarch.com/team/|title=National Committee|publisher=Women's March on Washington|access-date=January 1, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170101162318/https://www.womensmarch.com/team/|dead-url=no}}</ref>；前任美國新澤西小姐Janaye Ingram作為統籌策劃負責人<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.npr.org/2017/01/23/511267131/womens-march-organizer-we-are-committed-to-fighting-for-change|title=Women's March Organizer: 'We Are Committed' To Fighting For Change|last=|first=|date=January 23, 2017|work=|publisher=NPR|access-date=|via=|archive-date=2017-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126013916/http://www.npr.org/2017/01/23/511267131/womens-march-organizer-we-are-committed-to-fighting-for-change|dead-url=no}}</ref>。組織者表示這次活動並非針對川普，「更多是關於婦女權利的主動行動」。Sarsour表示這是「對社會公義和包含種族、族裔、性別、宗教、移民和醫保在內的人權議題的態度」<ref name="The Guardian" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Heyboer|first1=Kelly|title=Women's March on Washington 2017: Who's going and when, how to get there and why it's happening|url=http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2017/01/womens_march_washington_2017_dc_trump_when.html|work=The Star-Ledger|date=January 4, 2017|accessdate=January 4, 2017|archive-date=2017-09-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170912053046/http://www.nj.com/news/index.ssf/2017/01/womens_march_washington_2017_dc_trump_when.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

儘管如此，因為活動有大部分是反川普的人士參與<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/women-march-protest-president-trump.html|title=Defiant Voices Flood U.S. Cities as Women Rally for Rights|last=Chira|first=Susan|date=January 21, 2017|last2=Alcindor|first2=Yamiche|newspaper=The New York Times|issn=0362-4331|access-date=January 22, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122055946/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/21/us/women-march-protest-president-trump.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，有時候也直接將其稱為反川普遊行<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/jan/22/the-guardian-view-on-the-anti-trump-marches-nasty-women-of-the-world-unite|title=The Guardian View on the anti-Trump marches: Nasty Women of the world unite|date=January 22, 2017|newspaper=The Guardian|last=Editorial Board|issn=0261-3077|access-date=January 22, 2017|archive-date=2017-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122194035/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/jan/22/the-guardian-view-on-the-anti-trump-marches-nasty-women-of-the-world-unite|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

